<body style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; background-color: #ffffff;">
<h3 style="text-align: left; font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 6.00pt; margin-bottom: 2.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold;" color="#0000FF"
	 face="Arial" size="5">Sort</font></b> <b><font style="font-family: Arial;
													 font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold;"
													 face="Arial" size="5">Function</font></b></h3>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">Format:</font></b></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt; margin-left: 12px;"><font
	 style="font-family: 'Courier New';" face="Courier New">b =</font>
 <b><font style="font-family: 'Courier New'; font-weight: bold;" color="#0000FF"
			 face="Courier New">sort</font></b><font style="font-family: 'Courier New';"
													 face="Courier New">(group</font>
 <b><font style="font-family: 'Courier New'; font-weight: bold;" color="#0000FF"
			 face="Courier New">using</font></b> <span><font style="font-family: 'Courier New';"
															 color="#FF00FF"
															 face="Courier New">[</font></span><span
	 style="font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;">-</span><font style="font-family: 'Courier New';"
	 color="#FF00FF" face="Courier New">]</font><font style="font-family: 'Courier New';"
														 face="Courier New">item</font>
 <font style="font-family: 'Courier New';" color="#FF00FF" face="Courier New">[</font><b><font
	 style="font-family: 'Courier New'; font-weight: bold;" color="#0000FF"
	 face="Courier New">where</font></b> <font style="font-family: 'Courier New';"
												 face="Courier New">condition</font><font
	 style="font-family: 'Courier New';" color="#FF00FF" face="Courier New">]</font><font
	 style="font-family: 'Courier New';" face="Courier New">);</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">Description:</font></b></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">The
 <b><font style="font-weight: bold;">sort</font></b> function will sort
 occurrences of records or items based on the value of an item. It will
 order the multiple records or items in the specified group in ascending
 sequence <b><font style="font-weight: bold;">using</font></b> the specified
 data item as the sort key. The sort key item must be contained within
 the record or item sorted. If a dash (<span style="font-weight: bold;">negative
 sign</span>) is included before the item name, the sort will be in descending
 order. If a <b><font style="font-weight: bold;">where</font></b> condition
 is included, the function sorts only the occurrences for which the condition
 is true.</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 10.80pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">Sort</font></b> <font style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;"
									 face="Arial" size="2">is primarily
 intended for use in batch applications. It should be used with extreme
 caution in data entry applications because of possible conflicts between
 the operatorâ€™s actions and the program logic.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;
	 text-indent: 10.80pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">Return value:</font></b></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 12.00pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt;" color="#000000" face="Arial"
	 size="2">The function returns a logical value 1 (true) if successful
 and 0 (false) otherwise.</font></p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-left: 12.00pt; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;">&#160;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt;"><b><font
	 style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 10pt; font-weight: bold;" face="Arial"
	 size="2">Example 1:</font></b></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt; margin-left: 12px;
	 font-family: 'Courier New';"><font color="#0000FF">sort</font>(PERSON
 <font color="#0000FF">using</font> LINE_NUM);</p>
<p style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; margin-left: 12px;
	 text-indent: -12px;"><b><font style="font-weight: bold;">E</font></b>xample
 2:<br />
<span style="margin-top: 0.00pt; margin-bottom: 0.00pt; font-family: 'Courier New';
		 font-weight: normal;"><font color="#000000"><font color="#008000">//&#160;sort
 the children by age from oldest to youngest<br />
</font><font color="#0000FF">sort</font>(PERSON <font color="#0000FF">using</font>
 -AGE <font color="#0000FF">where</font> RELATIONSHIP = <font color="#FF0000">3</font>);</font></span></p>
